Interface StackADT<E>

Record Components:
V - - the data "value" that this list is associated with
public interface StackADT<E>
StackADT.java
Version:
1.0

A linear ADT that represents a "stack" type. A type of list that allows insertions and removals to be performed only at the front of the list. Enforces last-in-first-out (LIFO) behavior on the list. Think of it as a "stack" of plates. You can't get to the bottom without taking the top plates off first.

Within this data type, it is possible to:

"Push" a element to the top of the stack. If the stack is empty, push the element as the first element in the stack. The element must be a valid, appropriate data-type for this stack.

"Pop" the top-most element from the top of the stack. If there are no elements in the stack, return null.

Check if the list is "Empty". Return true if the list is empty. Return false if the list is empty.

"Peek" at the top-most element on the stack. If there are no elements in the stack, return null.

Author:
Mikael Ly

  • Method Details

    • push

      void push(E element)
      Insert an object to the top of the stack. If the stack is empty, push the element as the first element in the stack.
      Parameters:
      E - element - The element to be pushed to the front of the stack.
      Throws:
      UnsupportedOperationException - if push is not supported by this stack
      ClassCastException - if the "element" is an inappropriate type for this stack
      IllegalArgumentException - if some property of the element prevents it from being stored in this stack

    • pop

      E pop()
      Remove the top-most object from the top of the stack.
      Returns:
      the object that was removed off the top of the stack. null if there are no elements to remove.
      Throws:
      UnsupportedOperationException - if pop is not supported by this stack
      ClassCastException - if the "element" is an inappropriate type for this stack

    • empty

      E empty()
      Return a bool if the stack is empty. true if empty, false if there are still elements.
      Returns:
      true if stack is empty, false if stack still has elements.

    • peek

      E peek()
      Retrieve the top-most element without removing it from the stack.
      Returns:
      the element on the top of the stack. null if there are no elements to remove.
      Throws:
      ClassCastException - if the "element" is an inappropriate type for this stack
